annotation.TEXT: Okay, this still looks like kind of a mess, but it's less messy than last time, so let's just try playing this out. (LOL at the trapped enemies!)
Yes, it let me in! Now, hopefully I can win at least a few lives here...
Umm... I'm not trapped here, am I? No, I should be able to just jump over this whole mess...
I'm... not sure what to make of all this!
Whoa, even the interior areas look like a war zone.
Alright, 5 extra lives isn't bad at all!
The shell isn't going to be very useful in this mess...
Okay, now this part can be mildly tricky, depending on who you're using. However, since Luigi's awesome when it comes to jumping, I can just leap over this whole setup!
Oh, man. So much murderall...
Unfortunately, the grass holding the potion back there is completely unreachable...
ZA WARUDO!
Demo count: 1
Okay, looks like I got out of that hairy situation.

Looks like all of these grass patches just hold radishes (I can't pick up the one that's cutting off the door, but I'll assume it's another radish). Now, as for the door, as long as the bottom half is intact, and there's a solid object right below it that you can stand on, you can enter it.
Alright, let's collect these murderall stars and murder Birdo with them!
Things look mostly neater this time...
Umm... Isn't there supposed to be a hawkmouth gate here that takes me to the next level? Or am I remembering wrong again?

Even worse, the vine is destroyed, so I can't backtrack, and I can't even suicide myself in a pit! I guess now's the time to input a code that's just as effective as the unmodified Konami code in Gradius III!
Okay, now let's collect some coins, pick up a mushroom to increase our life meter, and grab this cherry too...

Oh, what? Ah, this must be the Psycho variety of Birdo, who can magically materialize his eggs about half a screen to the left of him, which is perfect for surprise attacks and mind... games... mind... games... mind... games...
Well, that door's unreachable. Let's try Birdo's back door.
But, how can I proceed with the game now? Unless that white square is part of a functional door, and that scrambled Mouser block below it is solid...
Argh, not working. Well, maybe I can get it with the help of the mushroom block.
Well that explosion seems to have brightened up the sky to its normal hue. Still, I guess I've gotta watch out for booby traps like that in these messes.
Okay, the sky's back to normal again, and I'm not going to touch that chain this time.
Talk about your weird Beezos. It's like they're zombies now. Did Yoshika bite them?
Obviously that was a screen exit glitch. So, now the jars are conspiring against me?
ZA WARUDO!
Alright, let's get this duder out of the way so he doesn't bother me while I'm entering Subspace.
Heck, yeah. Beatin' up dudes with food.
Take THREE!!! Okay, no glitchy "S". That's good. Oh, and of course, the title screen background is supposed to be light green and not blue!
Okay, now the blue grass is solid, and these red ones fortunately aren't booby traps.

Unfortunately, if the coin never turns into a puff of smoke, it doesn't count. Also, what the heck happened to the vine over here? I can't proceed to the next area like this! I'll have to try for the back door again...
Wow, I was so expecting to get blocked off here, but I got lucky. Also, there's a brick block buried in the mountain for some reason.
MEGA KILL!
Is that a climbable chain up there?
Huh. The vine got cut off a bit, but it's no big deal. I can just jump on these convenient platforms to get up!
Unfortunately, I never picked up any coins on this trip, so no slots for me this time...
Fortunately, this side of the room seems to be mess-free.
Ah, much better! Hopefully I'll be able to enter the gate after beating Birdo this time...
3-hit combo! Marvelous!
Yep, even the interior areas have messes in them, but at least the vine's not blocked this time.
Interestingly, you can grab grass while standing on a solid object that's just to the left diagonally, but not from the right.
Huh. Those blue blocks seem even more out-of-place than usual... Whatever.
MULTI KILL!
Whoa. It's also a mess in here, too.
Ow...
Yeah, you die. I don't know why that code exists, but in a situation like this, it's better to lose a life than have to reset and lose all progress!
Okay, good.
Hello, this is SomeGuy712x, and welcome to... Super Mario Bros. 2! Yep, this may seem spur-of-the-moment, but I've suddenly decided to play through this game!
Ah, now this is how you normally summon a murderall star! One will normally appear after you've collected five cherries.
Murderall star power, go!
Whoa, what's with Beezo? That's not how it usually moves...
Okay, the background's back to normal, and I'm coming for you, Birdo!
Ha! That last coin counts! If you see the coin turn into a puff of smoke, it will indeed still count towards your total, even if it occurred outside of Subspace!
Gotcha that time! Ooh, a coin! And, as I said before, it counts when it turns into a puff of smoke, even if it wasn't gotten in Subspace!
Huh. That's weird. The POW's rubble lingered around for a few seconds there. Okay, whatever.
Luigi used Time Stop! Every fifth time you pick up a grass that would normally be a big vegetable, you'll instead get a clock that freezes the foes for about 8 seconds.
Alright, let's murder 'em all with our murderall powers! Also, be sure to pull up the grass next to the POW for a 1-up.
Oh, and I can't go back out the way I came in! My only hope to escape this room appears to be making a tricky jump towards the bottom of the vine!
Huh. There was a piece of sand I could dig there.
Gotcha! And it doesn't look like anything is impeding the gate, so I'm outta here!
Aha-D'oh!
Boo-yah! I hit the jackpot on the very first spin!

If you're lined up to pick up a mushroom block and a grass at the same time, the mushroom block will take priority. However, if you stand just enough on one side, you'll be able to grab the grass without grabbing the mushroom block instead.
Whoops! Mushroom blocks are also awesome for getting stuck in things! That glitch is actually easier to do than you'd think! (However, it doesn't work on the All-Stars version.)
Demo count: 3
Anyways, let's go beat up some Shyguys and stuff.
And that's it! Easy enough, and fortunately the scattered junk didn't impede me too much...
Oh, there it is! The numerous murderall stars must've hit the sprite limit and kept it from spawning at first. Also, I guess I'll battle Birdo again, just for hahas.
Ack! What's with this blood red background? Is this a lava cave now?
Or, maybe the nasty weather has already hit! Oh, god...
LUIGI WINS
Note: LOGOEA is also what caused me to teleport when I threw the POW near Birdo's back door during the second run.
Jar interior is gray, and the platforms have been shortened, but there's no mess, and I can get a 1-up!

...No, it's not just Subspace. I can't collect them in normal space either. I thought you could collect them, but maybe I'm remembering wrong and they're just for decoration? Oh, well. Let's POW some dudes!
GAAAMMMEEE!!! That harmless-looking piece of quicksand swallowed up my egg! I'll have to aim around it...
Bah! I thought I'd get away in time...
Whoops! Not what I meant to do. Well, this life's boned, but at least I get a 1-up to reimburse me.
BGM: SMB2 (NES) - AAPPAA
Umm... Was the sky always this gray? Maybe we're in for some nasty weather...
Oh, what the heck? This... is definitely not normal. I think my game's going Turbo on me. Still, I'm not going to unplug it yet. Let's try going back through the door...
Ooh, nice!
Okay, so here I go with take 2! (Ignore that weird thing on the "S" in "Bros.". I'm sure it's nothing.)
Oh, man. We've got these almost completely solid stripes here! I don't think I can even make it to Birdo this time!
Alright, get out of my way, Shyguy. I'm here to use this back door to the boss arena.
Hmm... I know the door is around here somewhere...
Huh. That's weird. I could've sworn you could collect those cherries. Maybe you can't in Subspace?
Oh, well look at that! Okay, I can continue the game, so I guess I'll keep playing...
OUCH!
Ack! Dang booby traps!
Yep... Whoa, geez!
Okay, you may have injured me there, Birdo, but that will be your downfall, as you sent me high enough to summon a murderall star! Now, die!
Okay, so if you pause the game, and then on controller 2, press Up, A, and B at the same time...
Umm... Huh... Did the music always sound like this? Well, maybe my memory's a little fuzzy...
FLAWLESS VICTORY
Oh, man, though. These messes are really going to mess with me... Hey, can I pick up that grass in there?
Okay, cool. Now, what's with this line of grass?
Mwahaha!
And now the sky is purple. This is getting freaky...
I'm pretty good at video games, by the way. (Note: The demo count was reset when I reset the game.)
ZA WARUDO!
Argh! The vine is blocked off, so I can't advance to the room above! Gotta backtrack for a moment...
KA-BOOOOM!!!
Ah! I knew you could collect those cherries!
D'oh! This grass is fake. I can't pull it. Man, I was hoping I'd be able to nail Birdo with a booby trap...
Huh. I don't remember this POW being here before, but it's cool to see it. What isn't cool is the fact that I can't seem to go any further towards Birdo's back door...
Yay! Okay, most of those spins were busts, but that opening jackpot and the two other hits gave me a total of 7 extra lives! Not bad!
DOUBLE FATALITY
Whoops! Well, that was a waste of a perfectly good shell...
Whoa, I missed my intended landing, but once again, got lucky and landed on something off screen.
And now the sky is a muddy brown, and we have our usual messes to deal with.
Demo count: 1
I'm going to go with Luigi again, because he's awesome!
Luigi used Teleport! It was painful, but still super-effective! Okay, that was weird, but very helpful, because I have no idea if I could've gotten over here otherwise.
I guess I'll enter Subspace again and pick up more coins and another mushroom.

Ah, that's more like it! Now this is the music that I remember! However, what's with all these floating blocks here? Are they part of the normal game? Well, there's a mushroom block here, so I may as well grab it.
Oh, man. I can't even enter the door over here! Although, strangely, I landed on something that's below the screen, so I didn't die at least.
Now, I think I can squeeze through that gap in the wall, maybe...
Yeah, that is really weird. I think maybe the color-changing sky is starting to get to the enemies...
Whoo-hoo! Every eighth enemy that dies and falls off screen should spawn a heart.
Hopefully, I can kill enough bad dudes (and perhaps ninjas that kidnapped the president) to earn a heart...
Huh. It looks like the oddly-scattered blocks are in different spots this time.
Careful. Some solid-looking objects may not actually be solid!

For whatever reason, the hawkmouth gate disappeared this time, not that it matters. Oh, one neat thing you can do with the flying carpet: If you go down so that you're partway off the bottom of the screen, you can move at running speed! (But don't go too low, obviously!)
Sweet! I nailed it! But, can I escape?
Huh. There's a floating piece of grass there? I wonder if I can pull it up...

Oh, that's interesting. When you throw an enemy during the clock's effect, it'll pass through anything solid. However, if the clock expires while the enemy is in mid-flight, it can end up landing in an isolated chamber like this, or possibly jammed in a wall!
Alright, well let's grab a mushroom and some coins, which I never did in the last level...
Okay, I don't care how messed up the game is this time. I want to keep playing. So, let's go to 1-2 with my main guy, Luigi!
And, whoops, the game just crashed! Well, I hope you all enjoyed watching me try to play SMB2! Good bye!
I guess I'll grab a mushroom and some more coins while I'm over here...
Mushroom blocks are awesome for flattening bad guys!
Whoa, that was close! That gravity-defying sand block up there nearly screwed up my jump!
Nuts. I almost caught that vegetable after it wrapped around the screen. That would've been cool.
Demo count: 2
Man, that mushroom block might've been nice to have, but I don't think I can reach it...

Okay, so here's how this works: For every coin you collected in the level, you get one try at the slot machine. If you get a non-cherry three-of-a-kind, you get a 1-up. If the left reel stops on a cherry, you get a 1-up. If the left and middle reels are both cherries, you get a 2-up. And, getting three cherries nets you the jackpot: 5-up!
Alright, it's boss time! I don't have any murderall stars this time, but they were overpowered anyway. Also, this appears to be a normal Birdo and not a Psycho Birdo this time.
Wait for it...
At least none of the junk here is preventing me from climbing back up...
Well, so much for a normal background. I guess I'll have to deal with this purple sky, and whatever messes this room has.
Alright, now let's go gambling!
What the? Argh! My coin!
Wow. Just wow. I guess we won't need the logs to cross the waterfall here this time!
Oh, right. Since I'm going off screen here, I get more stars! Huh, some blocks touching the top of the screen are vanishing for some reason...
Um, what? Did the game just send me back to start? Argh...
Oh, man! I must've completely forgotten about this aspect of the game! Jumping off screen makes a bunch of invincibility stars appear! Sweet!
FATALITY
What the deuce?
It must be spawning me under the screen. That's my guess.
Hmm... You know... After thinking about it, I don't think this game was functioning entirely properly back there, so I'm going to reset and start over.
Oh, by the way, I set a keyboard key to A button autofire, so I can navigate through tight spaces like this much more easily.
I'm going to go with Luigi, because he rules! Alright, now let's start the first level...
Now, it's rather obvious that the game wasn't functioning correctly there, so I'm going to try blowing in the cartridge and give this one more go...
I hope the 1-up is reachable...
Oh, cool! I was able to get another 1-up! (Normally, any 1-up grasses become radishes if you've already gotten a 1-up in the level, but of course, this game is being wonky right now...)
...Huh, what? No! The game won't let me into the gate because of all that junk in the way! Argh! I'm going to have to leave the area and come back and hope for a better layout!
Yeah, maybe they are. I can't even enter the second jar. But, fortunately, the key isn't needed to clear this level.
Now, we should be good to go! As usual, I'm picking Luigi, because he's THE MAN!
